title: Ferry delayed after harbour bomb find
text:
22 February 2017 at 7:34am Ferry delayed after harbour bomb find 
The Condor Clipper is currently holding off the Isle of Wight after what's believed to be an unexplored WW2 bomb was discovered in the Portsmouth harbour area. 
Royal Navy divers are on the scene and residents around the sea side area being advised to stay in doors.
